EmbeddedServiceFlowConfig.name: EmbeddedServiceFlowConfig
EmbeddedServiceFlowConfig.description: Represents whether an Embedded Service Flow feature is enabled or not.

EmbeddedServiceConfigId.description: The unique ID of an EmbeddedServiceConfig (the Embedded Service deployment) that the flow config is associated with.

Enabled.description: Specifies whether the embedded flow is enabled (true) or not (false). Defaults to false.

FullName.description: The full name of the parent object EmbeddedServiceConfig in Metadata API. The full name can include a namespaceprefix.

Metadata.description: The embedded service flow config's metadata.
